# AICP v84 — Protocol Backlog (repo-backed)

> Scope: **protocol only** (Core + extensions + registries + schemas + fixtures + conformance + profiles + implementer guides).
> Out of scope: platform/enforcer implementations, chat UX, agent internals, hosted trust services.

This backlog translates consumer adoption needs into **protocol deliverables** that can be shipped in-repo:
- RFC/Docs (normative)
- Registries
- JSON Schemas
- Golden fixtures (JSONL transcripts)
- Conformance suites + runner checks
- Profiles (bundle suites)
- Implementer tooling/quickstarts (adapter skeletons, CI templates)
- Snapshot + release discipline

## Current shipped baseline (as of v84)
- Core: envelope, hash-chain, message_hash, signatures verify, CONTRACT_PROPOSE/ACCEPT, CONTEXT_AMEND, ATTEST_ACTION, RESOLVE_CONFLICT, ERROR.
- Stable extension baseline includes: EXT-CAPNEG, EXT-ENFORCEMENT, EXT-POLICY-EVAL (with anchored registry refs and compatibility notes).
- Numeric canonicalization M16b is shipped: finite floats supported with deterministic ECMAScript-aligned tokens; unsafe integers remain rejected.
- Release discipline M18 is shipped: errata cadence doc + errata validator are part of `make validate`.
- M22 is started: channel properties schema/registry + CAPNEG negotiation fields + CN-09 MCP conformance evidence are in-repo.
- TB-HTTP evidence is shipped: `conformance/bindings/TB_HTTP_WS_0.1.json` + `fixtures/bindings/http-ws/*` + `conformance/report_bind_http_ws.json`.
- Snapshot discipline exists (manifest generation + validation gate).

